Title: The Mask / Son of the Mask

reviewText: The Mask: In Edge City, nice guy Stanley Ipkiss, Jim Carrey, gets sssmokin' when he wears the mask of Loki which releases the id that is normally suppressed. Cameron Diaz is in this film and Ben Stein plays Dr. Neuman who has coincidentally written a metaphorical book titled The Masks We Wear. I think Jim Carrey is funny.Son of the Mask:  Beyond Edge City is Fringe City. Ben Stein is the only recurring actor in the sequel. It is like a nonanimated cartoon. Jamie Kennedy and Traylor Howard ,of Monk, are a couple who have a son that was conceived while he was wearing the mask. Alan Cummings is Loki who is searching for his mask. This movie is more enjoyable if you can latch onto the sweetness of the family and overlook a few cinematic details.
Title: The Mask / Son of the Mask

reviewText: If you like Jim Carrey then this is the movie for you. It's action filled with fun, laughs and toe tapping music. Stanley, played by Carrey, finds a magical mask that turns him into a character unlike himself. This includes his dog.  The second movie 'Son of the Mask' is surprisingly fun to watch. This time Loki, some ancient god of mischief, comes in search of his Mask and that's when the fun begins.
Title: The Mask / Son of the Mask

reviewText: Not many people seem to like the sequel to The Mask, but I thought it was a pretty funny movie. I will admit it not as good as the first one, but it's rare when sequels can beat the first movie. Very good for the price and definitely would recommend for a good comedy double feature!
Title: The Mask / Son of the Mask
